		}
		{
			dependencies: ["40E6805C66BACAA1"]
			description: [
				"GregTech machines have a circuit option in their GUI, so when you see a recipe with that circuit, you need to select it. That effectively locks the machine into making only the recipies with that circuit. Of course you can change the circuit later. For multiblocks you need to set the circuit in input bus/hatch."
				" "
				"Also you can make the number choosing circuit from a normal circuit."
				""
				"Also also there is a AE2 addon that changes the circuit dynamically. Look into QOL quest chapter for more info."
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "gtceu:programmed_circuit"
				tag: {
					Configuration: 0
				}
			}
			id: "4875FB6628C1FCDC"
			min_width: 300
			tasks: [{
				id: "71AF3878DBC0AB29"
				title: "Yes I get it chief"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Programmed circuits"
			x: -1.0d
			y: 1.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["40E6805C66BACAA1"]
			description: [
				"Probably the hardest thing about GregTech, because there will be a time when you will have to use BASIC MATH!!! So lets get into the explanation."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"First: Voltage. It's pretty straight forward, this tells you how much energy can pass through a cable. Every cable has different values, so read carefully!"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Second: Amperage. You can think about amperage as a package that unboxes to voltage. Amperages (or packages) are sent from a providers, like energy converters (they always send the amount of amperage that they have in their name, eg. LV 1A energy converter sends 1A. In LV, 1A = 32V, and this will scale up in every tier. Cables also have a maximum amperage that they allow, if you give them more, they WILL burn!"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Third: You can't tier skip cables, meaning if the cable doesn't say it can transport LV energy, then it really can't."
			]
			id: "1988BDD7E065E6A6"
			tasks: [{
				id: "472EC5564C82AE35"
				title: "Energy system"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -1.0d
			y: -0.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["40E6805C66BACAA1"]
			description: ["You might have sees already that some recipes from GregTech have a different UI. It tells you the tier that you can craft the recipe, and also the exact time. If you click on the tier (eg. LV) you can change it so it shows you how would this recipe perform in other tiers."]
			id: "214AF983D9546F5B"
			tasks: [{
				id: "39C1BC730735419E"
				title: "Recipes"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: -1.0d
			y: -2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1988BDD7E065E6A6"]
			description: [
				"Energy converters convert FE to EU at a rate of 4:1. Solar panels are buffed so you can actually use them as a solid source of energy."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Because converters in this pack defaultly convert to the correct state (transforming FE -> EU), you dont have to use soft mallet on them."
				""
				"This technology was brought to you by aliens from different Stars. Thank you Star Technology!"
			]
			id: "01339A8C26CC6E0C"
			tasks: [{
				id: "2A9A4799091F0F7B"
				item: "gtceu:ulv_4a_energy_converter"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Energy converter"
			x: 1.0d
			y: -0.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["01339A8C26CC6E0C"]
			description: [
				"Each tier has its own superconducters, cables, which have no energy loss."
